 \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003391_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photo J. Prag\" src=\"ISic003391_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003391.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photo J. Prag\" src=\"ISic003391-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003391_leftdetail_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photo J. Prag\" src=\"ISic003391_leftdetail_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003391_leftdetail.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photo J. Prag\" src=\"ISic003391_leftdetail-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003391_rightdetail_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photo J. Prag\" src=\"ISic003391_rightdetail_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003391_rightdetail.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photo J. Prag\" src=\"ISic003391_rightdetail-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003391_context_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photo J. Prag\" src=\"ISic003391_context_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003391_context.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photo J. Prag\" src=\"ISic003391_context-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text from autopsy\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>(House of) Gnaius Modius\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Archaeologically, the 'baths of Cnaius Modius' (so called because of this inscription at the entrance) should be dated to the first century BC (so Tréziny 2018: 274), not the third-century BC as discussed in Torelli 2007\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> 2007.0671 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\" target=\"_blank\">http