ption at the entrance) should be dated to the first century BC (so Tréziny 2018: 274), not the third-century BC as discussed in Torelli 2007\u003C/p>  ",{"id":306,"html":307},"bibliography","\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> 2007.0671 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> 59.1107 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> 26.1102 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Manni Piraino 1975 152 no.18 tav.34.3 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001772\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001772\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Torelli 2007 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001558\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001558\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Tréziny 2018 273-274 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002599\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002599\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  ",{"id":309,"html":310},"handnote"," \u003Cp>Letters neatly formed of small black basalt stone chips. Nu has a shorter right hand vertical; omicron is equal size to the other letters; alpha off vertical, cross-bar formed by single piece; mu formed by four equal off-vertical strokes, mid-point descending fully to the base-line.\u003C/p> Line 1 \u003Cp> Types list: \u003Ca href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Α-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Α type1\u003C/a> \u003Ca href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Α-type1.3.html\" target=\"_blank\">Α type1.3\u003C/a> \u003Ca href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.gi